`ok` is definitely not _the_ way to ignore the return value. `let _ = ...;` has nearly 400 uses in `rust-lang/rust` (`git grep 'let _ =' | wc -l`), from a quick glance many of these are definitely ignoring results (but obviously not all; either way, orders of magnitude more than `.ok()`).
